<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Oil Pan, Vibration Damper, Oil
        Pump Water Pump, And Front Cover - Installation - Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="3">
        <title>Oil Pump</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>When installing the inner and outer gerotor, make sure the word "damper" is facing towards the
                    front of the engine. Failure to do so will result in engine damage.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200526" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figF13/F1315.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Inner Gerotor</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Inner Gerotor</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the inner gerotor over the crankshaft nose with the word "damper" facing the oil
                pump housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200527" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figF13/F1316.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing Outer Gerotor and Square Cut Ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer Gerotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Seal Ring</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the outer gerotor with clean engine oil. Install the gerotor in the oil pump
                housing with the word "damper" facing the oil pump housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pack cavities between and around the gerotor with an all purpose assembly grease to insure
                proper priming at engine startup.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install square cut seal ring in the oil pump housing groove.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figF13/F1318.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Oil Pump Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align dowel pins and install oil pump housing with seal ring and large gerotor gear onto
                crankshaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install four oil pump housing mounting bolts. Tighten bolts to standard torque value.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
